rdf:Description.rdfs:comment:
A citation in which the citing and the cited entities have at least one author in common.

In particular, like the parent class cito:Citation, cito:SelfCitation and its accompanying object properties cito:hasCitingEntity, cito:hasCitedEntity and cito:hasCitationCharacterization can be employed to reify direct citation statements made using the CiTO citation object property cito:cites or one of its sub-properties, accompanied by an additional statement using cito:sharesAuthorWith for linking the citing paper and the cited paper. 

For example, the following cito:SelfCitation resource

     :thisCitation a cito:SelfCitation ; 
          cito:hasCitingEntity :paperA ;
          cito:hasCitationCharacterization cito:extends ;
          cito:hasCitedEntity :paperB .

can be alternatively described as follows

     :paperA cito:extends :paperB .
     :paperA cito:sharesAuthorWith :paperB .
